  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed enclosure of the balcony creating a front facing dormer, would alter the appearance of the dwellinghouse to the streetscape and results in a loss of symmetry with its semi-detached dwellinghouse pair at No. 4 Leabank Close, forming an incongruous alteration to the host property, harming streetscape amenity and the character of the Sudbury Hill Conservation Area - Harrow on the Hill, with no public benefits outweighing the harm caused. The proposal is therefore contrary to Paragraph 131 of the National Planning Policy Framework (2023), Policy HC1 of the London Plan (2021), Policy CS1 of the Harrow Core Strategy (2012), Harrow Council Development Management Policies DM1 and DM7 (2013), Policy 4 of the Sudbury Hill Management Study (2008) and the Supplementary Planning Document Residential Design Guide (2010).&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;"
